Organ donation and transplant laws and procedures are changing.
In Russia, lawmakers consider law to allow local hospitals to do transplants.
US and Canadian officials are investigating China’s practice of harvesting organs from prison inmates.
Washington state legislators are considering changing laws to allow domestic partners to authorize organ donations.
Philippine government is attempting to develop better guidelines on organ donations.
US organ transplant guidelines are being changed to allowed heart transplants for infants with different blood types.
Zimbabwe is trying modernize its program for organ donations.
South Carolina is considering law to allow inmates to donate lessening prison terms.
